ency service<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Some of the most common problems that indicate you need our local emergency furnace repair include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Pilot light issues:\u00a0<\/strong>If your pilot light is discolored (yellow or orange instead of blue) or won\u2019t stay lit, it should be addressed by a professional ASAP.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Blower motor failure:\u00a0<\/strong>If your heater is running but not distributing warm air, it could be due to a malfunctioning blower motor.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Thermostat issues:\u00a0<\/strong>When you adjust the thermostat, but the heater doesn\u2019t respond, it\u2019s likely a thermostat-related issue.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Overheating:\u00a0<\/strong>If your furnace shuts down frequently or emits a burning smell, it\u2019s likely overheating and needs attention.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How do we handle heater emergencies?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>At Medley, we provide fast response times, so you don\u2019t have to wait in the cold. We also provide thorough troubleshooting and diagnostics to ensure we make the most accurate repairs possible. Our team repairs all types of heaters, including gas furnaces, electric heaters, boilers, and more.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While you wait for our arrival, we recommend blocking drafty windows and doors, dressing in layers, and using an electric space heater to stay warm.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">AC Emergencies: Restoring Comfort During Heatwaves<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Dealing with a broken AC in the summer is frustrating. Here are some tips to help you restore comfort during heatwaves and when you may need our emergency AC repair services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Signs you need emergency AC repair<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Look for these signs that indicate you need emergency AC repair:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Your air conditioning isn\u2019t cooling the air, or it\u2019s blowing warm air.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The AC unit is making unusual and\/or loud humming or grinding noises.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>You notice water leaking from the air conditioner.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The system suddenly shuts off or won\u2019t turn on at all.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>The coils are frozen or you notice excessive ice buildup on the unit.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Common AC problems requiring emergency service<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>If your AC isn\u2019t working, don\u2019t open the windows. This could make the problem worse because it\u2019s more difficult for the system to cool the indoor air once warm air from the outside enters your home.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some common AC problems that typically require emergency service:&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Refrigerant leak:\u00a0<\/strong>If your AC has low refrigerant or is leaking refrigerant, it can\u2019t cool your home efficiently.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Compressor issues:\u00a0<\/strong>If the AC won\u2019t turn on or can\u2019t cool your home effectively, it could be due to an issue with the compressor.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Electrical problems:\u00a0<\/strong>The circuit breaker may trip whenever your AC starts, indicating a problem with your electrical wiring or connection to the AC unit.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fan malfunctions:\u00a0<\/strong>When the AC fan won\u2019t spin or operates inconsistently, it should be repaired or replaced.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">How do we handle AC emergencies?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you call us, we\u2019ll arrive quickly to inspect and repair your home\u2019s central AC or mini-split ductless system. We\u2019re experts at resolving pressing AC issues like refrigerant leaks, frozen coils, electrical problems, and more.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>After we make repairs, we\u2019ll make sure your AC is performing optimally before we leave your home. If your AC stops working during a heatwave, change the air filter, check your circuit breaker, and call us immediately if the problem isn\u2019t resolved.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">The Importance of Addressing HVAC Emergencies Promptly<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you suspect a problem with your home\u2019s HVAC system, it\u2019s important to address the emergency promptly. Ignoring HVAC problems can lead to costly repairs or replacements and may lead to further damage.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When you address the issue quickly, you protect your home and family from safety risks like a dangerous gas leak, electrical fire, or overheating. Plus, prompt repairs help you maintain the comfort inside your home by keeping temperatures at a reasonable level and your HVAC functioning during critical times.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tips for Preventing HVAC Emergencies<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here are some helpful tips to prevent HVAC emergencies:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Get regular maintenance:\u00a0<\/strong>Schedule seasonal inspections and tune-ups for your heater and air conditioner. Good preventative maintenance helps you identify issues early before they turn into breakdowns or costly repairs.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Keep things clean:\u00a0<\/strong>Replace air filters per the manufacturer\u2019s instructions, and clean your HVAC components regularly to maximize airflow.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Know the warning signs:\u00a0<\/strong>Recognize and address early warning signs like unusual noises, odors, or performance issues before they escalate into a breakdown.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Practice proper system usage:\u00a0<\/strong>Set your thermostat at a reasonable level and avoid overusing your system. Consider investing in a programmable thermostat to maximize energy efficiency.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choose Medley for Your Emergency HVAC Repair Needs<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Medley Heating, Air Conditioning, &amp; Plumbing covers all HVAC syst